JOHANNESBURG - Umalusi CEO Dr Mafu Rakometsi on Monday announced that the Quality Education Council does not need an extension for the release of the 2022 matric results. READ: Matric results to be released on Thursday, confirms Umalusi Rakometsi said 19 January was always the agreed-upon date by all stakeholders. He added that media reports of an extension have created unnecessary anxiety among learners. Rakometsi was speaking during a media briefing hosted by Umalusi on the quality assessments of the 2022 examinations. READ: Matric results delay won't hamper tertiary admission process, assures Dhet He said that the reason the matric results will be coming late was due to the Covid-19 pandemic. "The schools started late in 2022 as a result of the knock-on effects of the disruptions of 2020 and 2021 [academic years]. The schools had to do a lot of catching up as the class of 2022 suffered the full impact of the pandemic."